# Security Implementation Plan for NAVISION

## Goal
Apply all banking security and role-based permissions requirements to the existing NAVISION project, ensuring it runs without errors.

## Constraints & Preferences
- Strict role-based permissions: System Administrator login via email+password OR username+password only
- No other role can log in using email
- Single default System Administrator account after installation
- Automatic login form detection (email vs username)
- Strict RBAC for all user management actions
- Role-specific dashboards with sidebar, top bar, notifications, profile, cards, charts, responsive design, dark/light mode, search
- Security features: RBAC, CSRF protection, password hashing, session management, login audit, action audit, file upload validation, permission middleware
- No public registration page
- Role-specific dashboards and approval workflow (ED, CFO, MD)
- Approval history and timeline
- Reports with filters and export options
- Rejection rules with mandatory reasons and notifications

